Package: HIDDA.forecasting
Title: Forecasting Infectious Disease Surveillance Counts
Version: 0.3.2
Authors@R: c(person("Sebastian", "Meyer",
                    email = "seb.meyer@fau.de", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-1791-9449")),
             person("Leonhard", "Held",
                    email = "Leonhard.Held@uzh.ch", role = "ctb"))
Description: The forthcoming Handbook of Infectious Disease Data Analysis (HIDDA)
    contains a chapter on "Forecasting Based on Surveillance Data".
    The R package 'HIDDA.forecasting' provides the data and code to reproduce
    results from both the univariate analysis of Swiss ILI counts
    and the age-stratified analysis of Berlin norovirus counts.
Depends: R (>= 3.2.0)
Imports: grDevices, graphics, stats, utils, zoo, scoringRules (>= 0.9.4)
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown, ggplot2, fanplot, surveillance (>= 1.16.0), forecast, prophet, glarma, MASS
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyData: TRUE
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
